reviews.text: The coffee was very nice though I like my flat white a tad hotter, this was borderline lukewarm and if you are still waiting for the lunch it will just not make it till the first bite. The roast was extraordinary though. The avocado salmon toast also had a very nice and unique taste, but here I found the toast a bit too crunchy. The place is very hip and stylish but maybe the chairs could be less stylish and more comfortable. All in all, it has all the elements of 5 stars, but not yet...

It's a beautifully designed environment and the coffee is good. However, when I visited, I noticed the baristas and staff tends to be rather surly. Maybe it was the early hours affecting their mood but a more sour and aloof  reception I couldn't find anywhere else in Hong Kong.
Extremely wonderful! A really nice place to go with friends ! Coffee is great, barista is wonderful and great food to add on. Super friendly service & extremely cosy atmosphere.
Terrible customer experience. Place is very fancy but the service is terrible.

I will say I love the vibe here as the cafe has a very bright and simple design. The coffee is good, and the food menu, while not extensive, is enough for a simple breakfast with a cuppa of good coffee. Very instagrammable cafe and I totally fall for the hype.

result.name: Omotesando Koffee Massmutual Tower

reviews.text: Still good but recently I felt the tamago sando (egg sandwich) bread is changed to cheaper one? Not soft at all and the bouncy of the egg was less than earlier when they just opened this new branch. A bit disappointed...

It's beyond my imagination that this place has so few reviews. Coffee here is absolutely amazing, the taste, creaminess, texture - and it's very consistent - it was equally delicious every single time I went there. The atmosphere inside really depends on how many people are there - the place is rather quiet. The interior is very simple and high quality - it's worth visiting even to just see it. Please mind, that to order a coffee you first need to go to the cash register - pay, take the receipt and only then go to the barista.

Omotesando Koffee is legendary amongst coffee aficionados. Starting with a single barista in a simple but very Japanese design house in Omotesando, there are now pop-up stores with a similar wooden decor spreading across Asia. Coffee here is pretty much as good as the original, with the bonus of having a lunch menu.
An amazing cup of coffee. Minimalistic decor, not the place where you will hang out for hours but a very good coffee
coffee is great and service with smile

result.name: Omotesando Koffee

reviews.text:
店舖走簡約風格，裝潢以木色、水泥色為主。入內點餐後經小樓梯到上層把單交給咖啡師，咖啡師便會按單沖調。開放式的設計，可以看到咖啡師沖調咖啡的整個過程。

雖然地方不大，但仍設有堂食區。座位設計相當慳位，可拉出和收入枱底，提升店內空間感。

Iced Cafe Mocha ($58)
咖啡味道香醇，濃郁芳香；朱古力醬味道甜美。兩者融為一體，於面層再加上了忌廉和可可粉，口感豐富，質感細滑柔順，餘韻令人回味再三。

The coffee was very nice though I like my flat white a tad hotter, this was borderline lukewarm and if you are still waiting for the lunch it will just not make it till the first bite. The roast was extraordinary though. The avocado salmon toast also had a very nice and unique taste, but here I found the toast a bit too crunchy. The place is very hip and stylish but maybe the chairs could be less stylish and more comfortable. All in all, it has all the elements of 5 stars, but not yet...

It's a beautifully designed environment and the coffee is good. However, when I visited, I noticed the baristas and staff tends to be rather surly. Maybe it was the early hours affecting their mood but a more sour and aloof  reception I couldn't find anywhere else in Hong Kong.
